## What the patch is
A byte-exact FORWARD `git show 3c27e17 -- src/angular/src/app/services/utils/rest.service.ts`.
It ADDS an already-shipped, clean, backward-compatible feature: it widens
`post(url)` to `post(url, body?: object)` and passes `body ?? null` to `_http.post`
so the four existing no-body callers are unaffected. Defect-free TypeScript/Angular
product code — the WebReaction pipeline (map/catchError/shareReplay) is unchanged.
Safe ON the API-contract/typing axis (A16 note): the optional param is
backward-compatible; no injection, no unhandled promise, no resource leak.

